#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: fn-typed-field
---

# function-typed case-class field passed to a HOF

Regression for the JS backend. A case-class field whose value is a function
(`View.step`) was emitted as a variadic lambda (`(...__a) => …`, whose `.length`
is 0), so accessing it as a *value* — e.g. handing `view.step` to `foldLeft` —
tripped `_dispatch`'s zero-arg auto-invoke and CALLED it (returning NaN /
"fn is not a function") instead of returning the function. A no-arg property
access on a case-class/enum instance now returns the data field as-is.

```scalascript
case class View[S](name: String, init: S, step: (S, Int) => S)

val v = View("sum", 0, (a, b) => a + b)

println(v.name)
println(v.step(1, 2))
println(List(1, 2, 3).foldLeft(v.init)(v.step))
```
